00:01:58.767 --> 00:02:02.501
So introduction
to Google Friend Connect.

00:02:02.501 --> 00:02:05.667
Google Friend Connect--
the reason it was created

00:02:05.667 --> 00:02:08.534
was to allow you to instantly
awaken and strengthen

00:02:08.534 --> 00:02:10.367
the communities
on your site.

00:02:10.367 --> 00:02:13.234
Basically what this means
is out of the box

00:02:13.234 --> 00:02:16.834
you can take
some copy and paste code--

00:02:16.834 --> 00:02:20.367
like Vic demo-ed in the keynote
with the elements--

00:02:20.367 --> 00:02:22.834
to a little bit more advanced
copy and paste code

00:02:22.834 --> 00:02:24.400
with Google Friend Connect,

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:26.634
and plug that
into your web site

00:02:26.634 --> 00:02:29.200
and instantly
allow people to log in

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:31.467
using the identities
of their choice

00:02:31.467 --> 00:02:34.167
done through
the OpenID protocol

00:02:34.167 --> 00:02:37.033
and also bring
their friends with them

00:02:37.033 --> 00:02:40.234
from social networks
that support OpenSocial.

00:02:40.234 --> 00:02:43.934
So after they're there and
they bring their friends in,

00:02:43.934 --> 00:02:46.133
they can then interact
with other members of the site,

00:02:46.133 --> 00:02:47.934
make new friendships,

00:02:47.934 --> 00:02:50.868
and then send
their activities on that site

00:02:50.868 --> 00:02:54.734
else--out elsewhere
on the web.

00:02:54.734 --> 00:02:56.567
So here's a little bit
of a demonstration

