Friend Connect's
a little bit different

00:10:53.767 --> 00:10:55.601
because--
because of two things.

00:10:55.601 --> 00:10:57.801
The first thing's audience.

00:10:57.801 --> 00:10:59.100
And so audience, you know,

00:10:59.100 --> 00:11:01.367
while you still want
to pay attention to, you know--

00:11:01.367 --> 00:11:03.133
the end user
ultimately is your goal--

00:11:03.133 --> 00:11:04.601
you know, these guys.

00:11:04.601 --> 00:11:06.501
There's a new audience
involved in Friend Connect

00:11:06.501 --> 00:11:09.267
that if you're doing
a traditional...

00:11:09.267 --> 00:11:13.033
OpenSocial gadget
you might not be aware of.

00:11:13.033 --> 00:11:14.601
It's a very powerful audience.

00:11:14.601 --> 00:11:16.167
And that's
the site administrator.

00:11:16.167 --> 00:11:18.200
So people who, you know--
sites that come along

00:11:18.200 --> 00:11:19.601
and decide to use
Friend Connect

00:11:19.601 --> 00:11:21.968
are people who, you know,
get a Blogger blog

00:11:21.968 --> 00:11:24.267
and want to use Friend Connect
gadgets on their Blogger blog.

00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:26.501
This is the individual
who is ultimately

00:11:26.501 --> 00:11:27.767
making the decision

00:11:27.767 --> 00:11:30.601
to install the gadget
on their site.

00:11:30.601 --> 00:11:32.634
So it's no longer
this kind of game

00:11:32.634 --> 00:11:35.467
around, you know,
how many community members

00:11:35.467 --> 00:11:36.701
can you get
to install this gadget,

00:11:36.701 --> 00:11:37.901
'cause they're not the one

00:11:37.901 --> 00:11:39.534
actually installing
the gadget anymore.

00:11:39.534 --> 00:11:41.133
They're just coming to a site
that's offering functionality,

00:11:41.133 --> 00:11:42.467
and that functionality
is functionality

00:11:42.467 --> 00:11:44.501
that you happen
to be providing.

00:11:44.501 --> 00:11:46.601
And that's very different
than needing to, like,

00:11:46.601 --> 00:11:49.167
you know, virally spread
your app as much as possible.

00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:51.434
Now, you do need to,
you know,

00:11:51.434 --> 00:11:53.501
kind of get in front
of site administrators,

00:11:53.501 --> 00:11:55.033
and so when you
do create a gadget--

00:11:55.033 --> 00:11:57.667
and Ryan'll
talk about this later--

00:11:57.667 --> 00:11:58.801
is you can list it

00:11:58.801 --> 00:12:00.601
in the Friend Connect
Gadget Gallery.

00:12:00.601 --> 00:12:02.067
And that's part of,
you know,

00:12:02.067 --> 00:12:03.634
a site administrator's
core experience

00:12:03.634 --> 00:12:04.901
when they sign up
for Friend Connect--

00:12:04.901 --> 00:12:06.567
there's a gallery
that's in the admin site

00:12:06.567 --> 00:12:08.234
that they can access
that will have

00:12:08.234 --> 00:12:10.334
third-party gadgets in it.

00:12:10.334 --> 00:12:12.334
And so the powerful part here

00:12:12.334 --> 00:12:13.968
is that, you know,
a single administrator

00:12:13.968 --> 00:12:15.167
can basically
take your gadget,

00:12:15.167 --> 00:12:16.434
put it on their site,

00:12:16.434 --> 00:12:17.834
and the distribution
of your gadget

00:12:17.834 --> 00:12:20.200
can literally go from zero
to hundreds, thousands,

00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:21.567
you know, millions,
whatever,

00:12:21.567 --> 00:12:24.434
depending on
the traffic of their site.

00:12:24.434 --> 00:12:26.267
But what that also means
is that the bar has been raised.

00:12:26.267 --> 00:12:28.834
So, you know, your gadget
needs to be more relevant,

00:12:28.834 --> 00:12:30.667
more reliable.

00:12:30.667 --> 00:12:32.801
If somebody's gonna trust
to put this on, you know,

00:12:32.801 --> 00:12:34.067
the home page
of their site

00:12:34.067 --> 00:12:36.300
or on every news story
page on their site

00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:38.234
if they want to put comments at
the bottom of all their stories

00:12:38.234 --> 00:12:41.367
or something--some other
equivalent functionality...

00:12:41.367 --> 00:12:43.300
a site owner
really needs to be, you know,

00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:45.067
comfortable and confident
taking your gadget

00:12:45.067 --> 00:12:46.634
and putting it alongside
their brand.

00:12:46.634 --> 00:12:49.868
So it needs to look good and
it needs to fit into the site.

00:12:49.868 --> 00:12:52.133
And, you know,
a way to think about it

00:12:52.133 --> 00:12:54.267
is, you know, how can you
as gadget developers

00:12:54.267 --> 00:12:56.167
really create assets
for these sites?

00:12:56.167 --> 00:12:59.033
How can you be something
that site owners depend on?

00:12:59.033 --> 00:13:01.000
You know, that's
a good position to be in

00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:03.434
as a--as a software developer.

00:13:03.434 --> 00:13:05.634
So--and as
I mentioned earlier,

00:13:05.634 --> 00:13:07.100
because of this new audience,
you know,

00:13:07.100 --> 00:13:09.033
there's that--
there's less need to, you know,

00:13:09.033 --> 00:13:11.234
try and spread your app
virally between people

00:13:11.234 --> 00:13:12.567
while Friend Connect
has that--

00:13:12.567 --> 00:13:13.767
as he showed some
of the invite stuff

00:13:13.767 --> 00:13:15.400
around inviting to sites--

00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:17.234
and more need to just
communicate the value

00:13:17.234 --> 00:13:19.801
to--to site administrators.

00:13:19.801 --> 00:13:22.100
So again, you're ultimately
creating, you know,

00:13:22.100 --> 00:13:23.434
an experience with
the end user, but, you know,

00:13:23.434 --> 00:13:25.300
the site administrators
kind of hold the keys

00:13:25.300 --> 00:13:26.767
to distribution.

00:13:26.767 --> 00:13:28.934
And you really need
to be focusing on relevance.

00:13:28.934 --> 00:13:31.234
So create something useful
that makes sense on a web site.

00:13:31.234 --> 00:13:33.234
And I'll talk about that
a little bit more

00:13:33.234 --> 00:13:34.400
in a minute.

00:13:34.400 --> 00:13:36.200
And also focus
on reliability.

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:37.868
Like, if your gadget is,
you know,

00:13:37.868 --> 00:13:39.868
down 10% of the time
and it doesn't load,

00:13:39.868 --> 00:13:41.934
like, that's probably
not gonna be on many sites

00:13:41.934 --> 00:13:44.100
for very long.

00:13:44.100 --> 00:13:46.267
So one last point
about audience

00:13:46.267 --> 00:13:49.567
before I kind of
go into my next point

00:13:49.567 --> 00:13:50.767
is that really
Google Friend Connect

00:13:50.767 --> 00:13:52.501
is about making
the web more social.

00:13:52.501 --> 00:13:53.968
And so,
this is a huge opportunity,

00:13:53.968 --> 00:13:56.367
I think, for you
as gadget developers

00:13:56.367 --> 00:13:57.834
to really light up
these latent communities--

00:13:57.834 --> 00:13:59.167
as Ryan mentioned--

00:13:59.167 --> 00:14:02.133
that already exist on millions
of existing web sites.

00:14:02.133 --> 00:14:03.701
And I think
the key thing to remember

00:14:03.701 --> 00:14:05.601
is that some of these users
will be the same users

00:14:05.601 --> 00:14:07.267
that you're used to seeing
on social networks,

00:14:07.267 --> 00:14:08.534
but there's also gonna be
a lot of people

00:14:08.534 --> 00:14:10.300
who, you know,
you've never seen before.

00:14:10.300 --> 00:14:11.734
There's gonna be
people out there

00:14:11.734 --> 00:14:13.634
that, you know, don't care
to join a social network,

00:14:13.634 --> 00:14:15.133
haven't joined a social network
yet, you know,

00:14:15.133 --> 00:14:17.133
don't like the idea
of social networks.

00:14:17.133 --> 00:14:19.667
But, like, you know, everybody
likes to be social.

00:14:19.667 --> 00:14:21.901
So you really--
I think there's the ability

00:14:21.901 --> 00:14:24.634
to reach kind of
that broader audience here.

00:14:24.634 --> 00:14:26.934
So the second big idea,

00:14:26.934 --> 00:14:29.200
I think, to think about
is context.

00:14:29.200 --> 00:14:30.701
You know, as I
just mentioned, right--

00:14:30.701 --> 00:14:32.467
you're out there
on the web.

00:14:32.467 --> 00:14:34.067
And it means that--
what that means

00:14:34.067 --> 00:14:36.133
is that the context
for a gadget

00:14:36.133 --> 00:14:37.801
is not a traditional
social network,

00:14:37.801 --> 00:14:39.567
you know,
profile page anymore.

00:14:39.567 --> 00:14:42.434
You're now in the sidebar
of a web site.

00:14:42.434 --> 00:14:44.801
You're now at the bottom
of every, you know,

00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:46.300
blog post on this site.

00:14:46.300 --> 00:14:48.234
You're really in--
in, number one,

00:14:48.234 --> 00:14:50.100
places that are
probably more visible,

00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:52.834
but number two,
just places that are different.

00:14:52.834 --> 00:14:54.834
So, you know, the...

00:14:54.834 --> 00:14:57.100
things that kind of
worked in one context

00:14:57.100 --> 00:15:00.267
might not work in--in this
Google Friend Connect context

00:15:00.267 --> 00:15:01.701
and vice versa.

00:15:01.701 --> 00:15:05.901
So let's talk about some
UI stuff really quick here.

00:15:05.901 --> 00:15:07.501
I am a designer.

00:15:07.501 --> 00:15:09.367
So this is a--
a screenshot

00:15:09.367 --> 00:15:10.834
of the Google
Social Web Blog--

00:15:10.834 --> 00:15:12.033
kind of simplified
a little bit,

00:15:12.033 --> 00:15:13.901
but this is
the basic gist.

00:15:13.901 --> 00:15:16.100
And so you see on the right
they've got the--

00:15:16.100 --> 00:15:18.567
just the default skinned Google
Friend Connect Members gadget

00:15:18.567 --> 00:15:20.467
embedded on there.

00:15:20.467 --> 00:15:22.133
But let's say
that the site administrator

00:15:22.133 --> 00:15:24.400
actually, you know,
really wanted a black--

00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:25.734
black background
and white text.

00:15:25.734 --> 00:15:28.467
And all of a sudden,
their web site looks like this.

00:15:28.467 --> 00:15:30.234
So content on the left

00:15:30.234 --> 00:15:31.901
kind of, you know...

00:15:31.901 --> 00:15:33.167
looks a little bit drab

00:15:33.167 --> 00:15:34.734
just 'cause I didn't do
a whole lot of hackery.

00:15:34.734 --> 00:15:36.767
But the thing on--
the pointer notices that

00:15:36.767 --> 00:15:38.033
that gadget really now
doesn't feel

00:15:38.033 --> 00:15:39.367
like part of the site.

00:15:39.367 --> 00:15:40.601
It's really standing out.

00:15:40.601 --> 00:15:41.901
And that's kind of
not what you want.

00:15:41.901 --> 00:15:43.667
That's gonna--
if there's no flexibility

00:15:43.667 --> 00:15:45.567
in your gadget,

00:15:45.567 --> 00:15:47.133
once I put this on here,

00:15:47.133 --> 00:15:49.000
I might find the functionality
neat for a little while

00:15:49.000 --> 00:15:50.467
but I'm just
gonna get used to it--

00:15:50.467 --> 00:15:51.868
I'm gonna--
I'm gonna start to see it

00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:54.367
as, like, kind of the wart
on my site, right?

00:15:54.367 --> 00:15:56.234
And so, you know,
you can fix that

00:15:56.234 --> 00:15:57.834
by, you know, adding
skinning to your gadget.

00:15:57.834 --> 00:15:59.200
And this stuff--
this is stuff

00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:01.200
that Ryan'll
talk about later.

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:04.801
But, you know, so this is what
an administrator might do.

00:16:04.801 --> 00:16:06.734
So this is using
just our admin site.

00:16:06.734 --> 00:16:09.367
You can change the--
the options, the colors on--

00:16:09.367 --> 00:16:11.634
on our default gadgets

00:16:11.634 --> 00:16:13.534
to kind of make it
feel a little bit more--

00:16:13.534 --> 00:16:15.567
like, more part of the site.

00:16:15.567 --> 00:16:18.067
This is also a good way
just to mention to--

00:16:18.067 --> 00:16:19.267
if you are
creating a gadget,

00:16:19.267 --> 00:16:20.834
and you really--
and you need to add skinning

00:16:20.834 --> 00:16:22.467
and you want to add skinning,
take your gadget,

00:16:22.467 --> 00:16:23.734
throw it onto a site

00:16:23.734 --> 00:16:25.968
with a black background
and white text,

00:16:25.968 --> 00:16:27.367
and that'll pretty much
tell you,

00:16:27.367 --> 00:16:28.968
you know,
help you along the way

00:16:28.968 --> 00:16:30.434
on what is--what's the stuff
on my gadget

00:16:30.434 --> 00:16:32.200
that's not yet skinnable
and needs to be?

00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:34.267
Because that will pretty much
make any element of your gadget

00:16:34.267 --> 00:16:36.367
stand out in a bad way.

00:16:36.367 --> 00:16:38.234
And so,
dropping it on this

00:16:38.234 --> 00:16:39.400
and really figuring out,
"Oh, yeah,"

00:16:39.400 --> 00:16:40.734
like, "I forgot to make
the border skinnable."

00:16:40.734 --> 00:16:42.000
Like, "I need to do that."

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:43.200
Or, "The inner borders
aren't skinnable."

00:16:43.200 --> 00:16:44.534
Like, "I need
to think about that."

00:16:44.534 --> 00:16:46.133
And obviously
that's how we came a lot of--

00:16:46.133 --> 00:16:47.667
across some
of our skinning options.

00:16:47.667 --> 00:16:50.634
We added some
as we went on.

00:16:50.634 --> 00:16:53.601
So, you know,
another thing

00:16:53.601 --> 00:16:57.601
to...think about
with regard to context,

00:16:57.601 --> 00:17:00.567
in addition to just the fact
that you're on the web site,

00:17:00.567 --> 00:17:03.000
is that, you know,
existing applications

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:04.367
that some of you
may have written--

00:17:04.367 --> 00:17:05.834
so if you have
written applications

00:17:05.834 --> 00:17:07.300
for OpenSocial containers--

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:08.701
they might not make sense
out on the web.

00:17:08.701 --> 00:17:11.400
So--or at least not
for all Friend Connect sites.

00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:13.067
So, you know, I don't like
to pick on people

00:17:13.067 --> 00:17:15.067
but, like, the zombie biting
app, for example.

00:17:15.067 --> 00:17:16.501
You know, the--
you know.

00:17:16.501 --> 00:17:17.834
The church that wants to add

00:17:17.834 --> 00:17:19.234
Google Friend Connect
to their site

00:17:19.234 --> 00:17:21.367
is not going to be interested
in the zombie biting app.

00:17:21.367 --> 00:17:22.734
And probably
not a lot of sites

00:17:22.734 --> 00:17:24.167
are going to be interested
in a zombie biting app

00:17:24.167 --> 00:17:25.667
I think is my larger point.

00:17:25.667 --> 00:17:27.467
There might be a few,
like the Halloween site--

00:17:27.467 --> 00:17:28.934
that's gonna love it.

00:17:28.934 --> 00:17:30.167
But you really have
to think about, like,

00:17:30.167 --> 00:17:31.767
the context
that you're in now.

00:17:31.767 --> 00:17:34.300
It's not...you know,

00:17:34.300 --> 00:17:36.968
little apps that users
can just pick up

00:17:36.968 --> 00:17:38.367
and play with
with their friends.

00:17:38.367 --> 00:17:39.667
I mean, this is something
that's really gonna be

00:17:39.667 --> 00:17:42.234
on the front of someone's--
someone's site.

00:17:42.234 --> 00:17:44.834
And so you just need
to just keep that in mind.

00:17:44.834 --> 00:17:46.601
So just to wrap up
this section

00:17:46.601 --> 00:17:48.601
and to get into
some design stuff,

00:17:48.601 --> 00:17:51.501
again, audience--
continue to focus on the user

00:17:51.501 --> 00:17:53.000
and all else will follow.

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:55.100
But remember
that administrators,

00:17:55.100 --> 00:17:57.000
you know,
are your distributors.

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.467
So be useful,
provide relevant functionality,

00:17:59.467 --> 00:18:01.100
and be reliable.

00:18:01.100 --> 00:18:02.701
And then context--
your application

00:18:02.701 --> 00:18:04.200
is part
of someone else's site.

00:18:04.200 --> 00:18:06.901
You need to think about,
again,

00:18:06.901 --> 00:18:08.300
the skinning options.

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:11.200
I'll get a little bit into
size options in a minute.

00:18:11.200 --> 00:18:12.834
But also think
about creating something

00:18:12.834 --> 00:18:14.567
that, like,
lots of sites can use.

00:18:14.567 --> 00:18:16.033
You know,
the good example

00:18:16.033 --> 00:18:17.601
I think that Ryan
gave to me

00:18:17.601 --> 00:18:19.901
was the example
of the real-time chat app

00:18:19.901 --> 00:18:21.167
that maybe
didn't work so well

00:18:21.167 --> 00:18:22.400
in a traditional
social network

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:24.334
because, you know,
the overlap of--

00:18:24.334 --> 00:18:25.567
if I have, you know,

00:18:25.567 --> 00:18:27.501
Jonathan's chat
and that's on my profile,

00:18:27.501 --> 00:18:29.300
you know, the number of
people visiting my profile

00:18:29.300 --> 00:18:31.133
at any one time
is probably small.

00:18:31.133 --> 00:18:32.868
Probably me.

00:18:32.868 --> 00:18:34.567
But the, you know,
the overlap

00:18:34.567 --> 00:18:37.100
of if I put real-time chat
on, you know,

00:18:37.100 --> 00:18:38.501
the front page of something

00:18:38.501 --> 00:18:40.567
that's getting hundreds
of thousands of visitors a day--

00:18:40.567 --> 00:18:42.834
or even thousands
or hundreds of visitors a day--

00:18:42.834 --> 00:18:44.467
there's--there's at least
a higher chance

00:18:44.467 --> 00:18:46.067
of there being overlap
and it being useful.

00:18:46.067 --> 00:18:50.334
So just think about that.

00:18:50.334 --> 00:18:52.734
All right.

00:18:52.734 --> 00:18:54.300
Whoa.

00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:59.300
I think that, you know,
once you have that good idea

00:18:59.300 --> 00:19:00.667
that you need to give it

00:19:00.667 --> 00:19:02.167
kind of the good UI
that it deserves.

00:19:02.167 --> 00:19:03.934
And so my goal is
when you walk out of here

00:19:03.934 --> 00:19:06.000
to basically have
the basic gadget--

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.868
the basic structure of gadget
as I see it,

00:19:07.868 --> 00:19:09.968
and then also
just the tools to get started

00:19:09.968 --> 00:19:12.501
thinking about,
if you have an idea,

00:19:12.501 --> 00:19:14.868
how you might start
just sketching out

00:19:14.868 --> 00:19:16.667
what that might look like.

00:19:16.667 --> 00:19:18.634
And so we've created
a few gadgets ourselves,

00:19:18.634 --> 00:19:19.868
and I have
some experience there,

00:19:19.868 --> 00:19:21.033
so I just wanted
to kind of walk through

00:19:21.033 --> 00:19:22.868
some of this stuff.

00:19:22.868 --> 00:19:24.167
So, you know,
first you have,

00:19:24.167 --> 00:19:25.934
you know,
the gadget itself.

00:19:25.934 --> 00:19:28.567
Some of our gadgets
look like this.

00:19:28.567 --> 00:19:29.801
But they can also
look like this.

00:19:29.801 --> 00:19:31.167
They can be wide.

00:19:31.167 --> 00:19:32.467
And the point here
is just that

00:19:32.467 --> 00:19:33.801
there is no default size.

00:19:33.801 --> 00:19:36.133
So on traditional
social networks,

00:19:36.133 --> 00:19:37.501
you'll often have a size

00:19:37.501 --> 00:19:39.634
or set of sizes
for the profile view.

00:19:39.634 --> 00:19:41.767
You know,
the size is whatever--

00:19:41.767 --> 00:19:44.467
you know, IFRAME
or whatever div,

00:19:44.467 --> 00:19:46.734
like, the administrator
dumps it into, right?

00:19:46.734 --> 00:19:50.467
And so that
can be configurable through--

00:19:50.467 --> 00:19:52.467
we offer configuration
options for that,

00:19:52.467 --> 00:19:54.000
that you can expose
to the administrator

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:55.968
so you can adapt to that.

00:19:55.968 --> 00:19:58.133
But you need to make sure
that you're kind of

00:19:58.133 --> 00:19:59.567
building that into your app.

00:19:59.567 --> 00:20:02.467
And so, you know,
a good example here

00:20:02.467 --> 00:20:04.667
is the--
the comments gadget.

00:20:04.667 --> 00:20:08.667
And so, you know, it works
well in this smaller size

00:20:08.667 --> 00:20:11.267
and, you know, text expands
as you open it up.

00:20:11.267 --> 00:20:12.767
Just stuff
you expect it to do.

00:20:12.767 --> 00:20:14.534
But if I take
the comments gadget

00:20:14.534 --> 00:20:15.834
and maybe, you know,

00:20:15.834 --> 00:20:18.467
make some intentionally bad
design decisions--

00:20:18.467 --> 00:20:19.601
you could see, like,

00:20:19.601 --> 00:20:20.901
maybe you wanted to be
super descriptive

00:20:20.901 --> 00:20:22.234
and we wanted to call it

00:20:22.234 --> 00:20:23.801
the "Comments
&amp; Conversations" gadget.

00:20:23.801 --> 00:20:26.300
But, you know, that's
not gonna work in sidebars

00:20:26.300 --> 00:20:27.934
that are less
than 200 pixels,

00:20:27.934 --> 00:20:29.467
which is a lot of sidebars.

00:20:29.467 --> 00:20:31.834
Or, you know,
if you look closely,

00:20:31.834 --> 00:20:33.234
you can see--
it's hard to see up here,

00:20:33.234 --> 00:20:35.400
but a lot of the comments
are actually getting cut off.

00:20:35.400 --> 00:20:36.734
And maybe that's
because there was a div

00:20:36.734 --> 00:20:38.067
that was floating
over on the right

00:20:38.067 --> 00:20:39.734
that's now been brought over
and is overlapping

00:20:39.734 --> 00:20:41.734
some of the text.

00:20:41.734 --> 00:20:43.934
Down in the footer,
where we've got some navigation,

00:20:43.934 --> 00:20:45.501
we also wanted to put
a big call to action

00:20:45.501 --> 00:20:47.133
that says, "Leave a comment."

00:20:47.133 --> 00:20:49.367
You know, again, now that
that size has come down,

00:20:49.367 --> 00:20:51.868
that text is starting
to overlap and not look so nice.

00:20:51.868 --> 00:20:54.601
So you really need
to think about

00:20:54.601 --> 00:20:56.033
kind of how size--

00:20:56.033 --> 00:20:59.667
what role size
is going to play in your app.

00:20:59.667 --> 00:21:03.434
And I'll go into what I think
a good minimum size is,

00:21:03.434 --> 00:21:04.968
but one thing
I want to mention first

00:21:04.968 --> 00:21:07.033
is just that text
can often be the long pole.

00:21:07.033 --> 00:21:10.033
So, you know,
the two examples here--

00:21:10.033 --> 00:21:11.868
the title and the footer.

00:21:11.868 --> 00:21:13.167
But if you're
going into a sidebar

00:21:13.167 --> 00:21:15.734
that's going to be
160, 180, 200 pixels,

00:21:15.734 --> 00:21:17.200
you really need
to be thinking about,

00:21:17.200 --> 00:21:19.467
"Oh, can I actually
fit in navigation

00:21:19.467 --> 00:21:20.667
and a call to action here?"

00:21:20.667 --> 00:21:22.667
Can I fit in, you know,
all these, you know--

00:21:22.667 --> 00:21:24.434
What's my longest case?

00:21:24.434 --> 00:21:25.901
Like, when I navigate
into a collection

00:21:25.901 --> 00:21:27.267
and I have previous,
and next,

00:21:27.267 --> 00:21:29.133
and then I want to offer
some, you know,

00:21:29.133 --> 00:21:30.868
navigation to get
back up the hierarchy--

00:21:30.868 --> 00:21:32.634
like, are those
all going to fit?

00:21:32.634 --> 00:21:35.534
And then think about
that for German

00:21:35.534 --> 00:21:38.234
or think about that for--
if you want to localize, right,

00:21:38.234 --> 00:21:39.667
like, double it.

00:21:39.667 --> 00:21:42.400
So it's--it's not--
it's not an easy problem.

00:21:42.400 --> 00:21:43.601
It's just something
to be aware of,

00:21:43.601 --> 00:21:45.033
and I don't have
a super good answer for you

00:21:45.033 --> 00:21:46.400
about how to avoid it,

00:21:46.400 --> 00:21:47.968
except for to go through
the states of your app

00:21:47.968 --> 00:21:49.601
and see, like--
what are the, you know,

00:21:49.601 --> 00:21:50.901
what are those complex cases

00:21:50.901 --> 00:21:52.234
that really might
load up an area

00:21:52.234 --> 00:21:54.434
with either navigation or--

00:21:54.434 --> 00:21:56.501
or something you might be
doing in your content area

00:21:56.501 --> 00:21:58.133
of your app.

00:21:58.133 --> 00:22:00.167
So I mentioned I'd give you
a good minimum size

00:22:00.167 --> 00:22:01.968
to focus on.

00:22:01.968 --> 00:22:04.100
This is kind of what I--
what I...

00:22:04.100 --> 00:22:06.067
have been following
in most of my design.

00:22:06.067 --> 00:22:08.100
And the reason is
is that most sidebars

00:22:08.100 --> 00:22:10.100
kind of fit in here.

00:22:10.100 --> 00:22:12.033
And designing any smaller
is really, really hard

00:22:12.033 --> 00:22:13.734
and annoying.

00:22:13.734 --> 00:22:15.534
And so, for example--

00:22:15.534 --> 00:22:18.334
but it really matters,
I guess...

00:22:18.334 --> 00:22:19.701
on the audience
that you're targeting.

00:22:19.701 --> 00:22:22.067
So if you're targeting,
you know, bloggers

00:22:22.067 --> 00:22:23.901
that use Blogger,

00:22:23.901 --> 00:22:27.100
and you want them
to be people

00:22:27.100 --> 00:22:28.300
that are going
to adopt your gadget,

00:22:28.300 --> 00:22:29.434
well, there's a lot
of Blogger templates

00:22:29.434 --> 00:22:31.267
that are 160-pixel-wide
sidebars.

00:22:31.267 --> 00:22:34.167
And so you better make sure
that your gadget looks good

00:22:34.167 --> 00:22:36.033
in those templates.

00:22:36.033 --> 00:22:37.501
And the same goes
for any other thing.

00:22:37.501 --> 00:22:40.400
Like, you know, WordPress
has sets of templates.

00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:43.267
There's content kind of
management things

00:22:43.267 --> 00:22:45.067
that a lot of sites use that--
to throw sites up

00:22:45.067 --> 00:22:46.634
that have
a lot of standards.

00:22:46.634 --> 00:22:48.868
I've found that, you know,
if you're designing, you know,

00:22:48.868 --> 00:22:50.567
180 pixels is probably--

00:22:50.567 --> 00:22:52.167
you're gonna hit
most people there.

00:22:52.167 --> 00:22:55.901
But again, some of the blogs
go down to 160.

00:22:55.901 --> 00:22:59.000
So let's talk about some
of the--some more structures.

00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:01.000
So there's the header.

00:23:01.000 --> 00:23:03.834
What I'm kind of showing here
is that, you know,

00:23:03.834 --> 00:23:07.000
the header hopefully
should be optional.

00:23:07.000 --> 00:23:09.601
What we're finding
as we go on

00:23:09.601 --> 00:23:10.834
is that, you know,
a lot of sites

00:23:10.834 --> 00:23:12.968
already have, you know,
systems in place

00:23:12.968 --> 00:23:14.434
either in their--
I had mentioned templates

00:23:14.434 --> 00:23:15.901
and Blogger
is one example.

00:23:15.901 --> 00:23:18.033
But there's other web sites
that already have

00:23:18.033 --> 00:23:20.834
systems for basically
blocking off their content

00:23:20.834 --> 00:23:22.400
and presenting it.

00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:24.000
And so you kind of
have to think about, you know,

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:26.000
making that--that header,
you know, toggleable.

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:28.234
So the--the takeaway
is not to put...

00:23:28.234 --> 00:23:30.767
you know, mandatory
functionality up in your header

00:23:30.767 --> 00:23:32.734
and to make that
basically toggleable

00:23:32.734 --> 00:23:35.200
by the--
by the site administrator.

00:23:35.200 --> 00:23:37.868
The next piece
is the footer

00:23:37.868 --> 00:23:41.000
where we commonly
throw navigation.

00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:42.234
And I think--

00:23:42.234 --> 00:23:44.067
if there was something
I was going to recommend

00:23:44.067 --> 00:23:45.534
as a principle
to stick to,

00:23:45.534 --> 00:23:47.200
this would be one of them,
which is--

00:23:47.200 --> 00:23:48.434
a lot of the gadgets
we've made

00:23:48.434 --> 00:23:50.200
and I think
all of the gadgets

00:23:50.200 --> 00:23:52.901
that we have seen
third-party developers make--

00:23:52.901 --> 00:23:54.467
at least everyone I've seen--

00:23:54.467 --> 00:23:56.501
have been putting navigation
down in the footer like this.

00:23:56.501 --> 00:23:58.400
And I think it's something
that's worked really well

00:23:58.400 --> 00:24:00.067
as far as
users can expect

00:24:00.067 --> 00:24:01.901
that when they're
in the middle of a collection

00:24:01.901 --> 00:24:03.234
that they can look down there

00:24:03.234 --> 00:24:04.868
and go through
the navigation like that.

00:24:04.868 --> 00:24:06.434
And so that's one--

00:24:06.434 --> 00:24:07.834
one thing I would
be recommending.

00:24:07.834 --> 00:24:10.868
So here's an example of--
I'm--maybe I was in--

00:24:10.868 --> 00:24:13.634
I was looking
at the Members gadget

00:24:13.634 --> 00:24:15.667
at was looking
at a set of my friends.

00:24:15.667 --> 00:24:17.467
And maybe
I clicked in on that

00:24:17.467 --> 00:24:20.534
and what I got was--
got to this collection,

00:24:20.534 --> 00:24:22.033
so now I can page through it.

00:24:22.033 --> 00:24:23.868
But you'll also
notice now

00:24:23.868 --> 00:24:25.300
there's a link
to go back in there.

00:24:25.300 --> 00:24:27.801
Because not only have I started
navigating hierarchically,

00:24:27.801 --> 00:24:30.434
but now I'm paging
through a collection.

00:24:30.434 --> 00:24:32.067
And if somebody
pages into a collection

00:24:32.067 --> 00:24:33.701
five, six, seven pages deep,

00:24:33.701 --> 00:24:35.300
do you really want
to have them--

00:24:35.300 --> 00:24:37.868
have to have them page
all the way back out

00:24:37.868 --> 00:24:39.634
to just get back
to the previous screen?

00:24:39.634 --> 00:24:40.934
So you need
to start thinking about

00:24:40.934 --> 00:24:44.467
how is the user--
how is the user navigating?

00:24:44.467 --> 00:24:49.534
And then one piece
that isn't really, you know,

00:24:49.534 --> 00:24:52.167
part of, I guess,
a gadget proper--

00:24:52.167 --> 00:24:53.834
it's kind of the other view
of it--is the Canvas mode.

00:24:53.834 --> 00:24:55.200
And it's
the same type of mode

00:24:55.200 --> 00:24:57.067
if you're used to developing
OpenSocial gadgets

00:24:57.067 --> 00:24:59.534
that you'll--
that you'll recognize.

00:24:59.534 --> 00:25:02.934
It's basically
a larger view of a--

00:25:02.934 --> 00:25:05.100
of a guaranteed
view size.

00:25:05.100 --> 00:25:07.667
And so, kind of
the recommendation I have

00:25:07.667 --> 00:25:09.701
is to basically take users
there when it makes sense.

00:25:09.701 --> 00:25:11.834
So a good example is

00:25:11.834 --> 00:25:14.801
you are, you know, an app
that does photo tagging.

00:25:14.801 --> 00:25:17.634
And you have--
a user is trying to--

00:25:17.634 --> 00:25:18.968
to tag photos,

00:25:18.968 --> 00:25:21.634
and the site administrator
has graciously given you

00:25:21.634 --> 00:25:25.234
160 pixels wide by, you know,
300 pixels tall,

00:25:25.234 --> 00:25:27.434
and they're trying to tag
faces in a photo.

00:25:27.434 --> 00:25:29.334
So you can either
give them, you know,

00:25:29.334 --> 00:25:30.968
a 50x50 photo

00:25:30.968 --> 00:25:32.300
and have them
try and tag faces--

00:25:32.300 --> 00:25:34.133
which probably won't
be very successful,

00:25:34.133 --> 00:25:36.367
'cause each face will be
about 6 pixels big--

00:25:36.367 --> 00:25:38.501
or you can take them
off to Canvas mode,

00:25:38.501 --> 00:25:40.234
where you might have
a larger view of that photo.

00:25:40.234 --> 00:25:42.901
And then it will allow them
to work in that space,

00:25:42.901 --> 00:25:45.334
and then when they're done,
you know, bring them back.

00:25:45.334 --> 00:25:48.667
And so, again, when thinking
about Canvas mode,

00:25:48.667 --> 00:25:49.934
thinking about using it

00:25:49.934 --> 00:25:51.801
kind of as a place
to take people

00:25:51.801 --> 00:25:54.701
when they really need
to kind of stretch their legs

00:25:54.701 --> 00:25:56.367
and get a little bit deeper--

00:25:56.367 --> 00:25:57.868
for the Members gadget,
for example, one thing we do

00:25:57.868 --> 00:26:00.701
when you go into--
but Canvas mode is we, you know,

00:26:00.701 --> 00:26:02.434
show the names of the members
next to the photo,

00:26:02.434 --> 00:26:03.767
'cause we have
that extra space.

00:26:03.767 --> 00:26:05.033
So if you're looking
for someone in particular,

00:26:05.033 --> 00:26:07.701
you can--
you can get to that.

00:26:07.701 --> 00:26:09.200
Cool.

00:26:09.200 --> 00:26:11.434
So those are just some of the
basic structures of a gadget,

00:26:11.434 --> 00:26:14.200
and now I just want to give you,
in closing here,

00:26:14.200 --> 00:26:16.601
just a framework to kind of
maybe start thinking about,

00:26:16.601 --> 00:26:18.868
you know, how--
how do I take the idea

00:26:18.868 --> 00:26:21.634
that, you know, I have now--
I know the basic structure.

00:26:21.634 --> 00:26:23.067
How do I actually start,
you know,

00:26:23.067 --> 00:26:26.033
filling that content area
with stuff?

00:26:26.033 --> 00:26:30.167
So...

00:26:30.167 --> 00:26:32.901
I guess the framework
I want to present is this.

00:26:32.901 --> 00:26:36.133
So if you think
about your gadget

00:26:36.133 --> 00:26:38.167
as having kind of
three key components to it--

00:26:38.167 --> 00:26:39.934
so you think about objects,

00:26:39.934 --> 00:26:41.601
you think about
user contribution,

00:26:41.601 --> 00:26:43.033
and think about
user consumption.

00:26:43.033 --> 00:26:45.367
And I'll explain this
with some examples.

00:26:45.367 --> 00:26:47.400
So first you start
with objects.

00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:49.067
So this is the--
the comments gadget.

00:26:49.067 --> 00:26:50.901
So the object
in our comments gadget

00:26:50.901 --> 00:26:52.767
is the comment itself.

00:26:52.767 --> 00:26:55.234
The user contribution
is kind of the posting UI

00:26:55.234 --> 00:26:59.133
for--for the user to post--
for users to post a comment.

00:26:59.133 --> 00:27:01.734
And then the consumption
is just, you know,

00:27:01.734 --> 00:27:04.300
that collection of comments

00:27:04.300 --> 00:27:08.601
that members can
page through to--to view.

00:27:08.601 --> 00:27:10.334
The Members gadget--

00:27:10.334 --> 00:27:12.100
the object is the member.

00:27:12.100 --> 00:27:14.000
The user contribution
side of it

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:15.234
is the joining of the site,

00:27:15.234 --> 00:27:16.567
the becoming a member
of that site,

00:27:16.567 --> 00:27:18.267
adding yourself
to that collection.

00:27:18.267 --> 00:27:20.234
And the user consumption
piece of it

00:27:20.234 --> 00:27:21.767
is just that, you know,

00:27:21.767 --> 00:27:23.701
viewing that collection,
paging through that collection.

00:27:23.701 --> 00:27:26.901
And of course this
is an oversimplification.

00:27:26.901 --> 00:27:28.567
Both of these gadgets do more.

00:27:28.567 --> 00:27:30.300
You can reply
to individual comments

00:27:30.300 --> 00:27:31.734
and those are different.

00:27:31.734 --> 00:27:34.234
You can click on someone's
face, view their profile.

00:27:34.234 --> 00:27:35.667
But again--
those are all objects

00:27:35.667 --> 00:27:37.601
that have user contribution
pieces to them

00:27:37.601 --> 00:27:39.367
and user consumption
pieces to them.

00:27:39.367 --> 00:27:41.067
So just starting off,
thinking about,

00:27:41.067 --> 00:27:42.434
"Okay, here's the idea I have

00:27:42.434 --> 00:27:45.200
for my--
for my gadget."

00:27:45.200 --> 00:27:47.534
And just starting to determine--
what are the objects?

00:27:47.534 --> 00:27:48.901
How do I let users
contribute those?

00:27:48.901 --> 00:27:50.400
How am I going
to display those to users?

00:27:50.400 --> 00:27:52.267
And just start, you know,
kind of sketching that out

00:27:52.267 --> 00:27:54.133
will be a big help in,
I think,

00:27:54.133 --> 00:27:57.267
getting you on the road to
creating a really good gadget.

00:27:57.267 --> 00:28:01.667
So one example that--
that I came up with that I like

00:28:01.667 --> 00:28:04.133
is to show that
this kind of can apply

00:28:04.133 --> 00:28:05.434
to things
that maybe just aren't,

00:28:05.434 --> 00:28:07.868
you know, kind of
the gadgets we've made,

00:28:07.868 --> 00:28:09.434
the comments gadgets,
stuff like that--

00:28:09.434 --> 00:28:14.200
is let's imagine that you've
written an interactive game

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:16.834
where, you know,
the main...

00:28:16.834 --> 00:28:18.868
the main interaction
the user has

00:28:18.868 --> 00:28:20.601
is with
an interactive game itself--

00:28:20.601 --> 00:28:24.634
not, you know,
something you're doing...

00:28:24.634 --> 00:28:27.000
in the, or, sorry,
not--not in the gadget,

00:28:27.000 --> 00:28:29.300
but it's with a game
where you're not

00:28:29.300 --> 00:28:32.067
interacting with normal
kind of UI components,

00:28:32.067 --> 00:28:33.801
that you're actually,
you know, you've got a custom UI

00:28:33.801 --> 00:28:35.067
and stuff like that.

00:28:35.067 --> 00:28:37.467
The stuff that comes out
of that game, right, are scores.

00:28:37.467 --> 00:28:38.901
And so, I think about--

00:28:38.901 --> 00:28:40.267
when you think about
a score object,

00:28:40.267 --> 00:28:42.133
in that model that
I just was talking about,

00:28:42.133 --> 00:28:44.400
you kind of get the--
the idea

00:28:44.400 --> 00:28:47.601
that, you know, users
are generating these objects,

00:28:47.601 --> 00:28:49.601
that they're--want to be able
to contribute to these objects,

00:28:49.601 --> 00:28:51.667
that they want to be able to
share these with their friends,

00:28:51.667 --> 00:28:52.934
other people on the site,

00:28:52.934 --> 00:28:54.801
contribute it to our
leaderboard, whatever it is.

00:28:54.801 --> 00:28:56.834
And then
the consumption side--

00:28:56.834 --> 00:28:58.167
somebody's who's just
gotten the high score

00:28:58.167 --> 00:28:59.834
wants to be able
to compare against other people

00:28:59.834 --> 00:29:02.267
and see where they fall
kind of in the ranks.

00:29:02.267 --> 00:29:04.100
And so just by thinking
about, you know,

00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:07.934
that basic idea of, "Okay, what
are the objects in my game?"

00:29:07.934 --> 00:29:09.801
You know, okay, well,
the score comes out at the end

00:29:09.801 --> 00:29:11.367
when they die,
et cetera.

00:29:11.367 --> 00:29:13.167
You know, you come up
with a concept of leaderboards,

00:29:13.167 --> 00:29:15.467
and I think that's...

00:29:15.467 --> 00:29:18.100
I don't--it was
interesting to me, I guess.

00:29:18.100 --> 00:29:21.334
So figuring out kind of
what your base object will be,

00:29:21.334 --> 00:29:23.434
how you're going
to display those objects,

00:29:23.434 --> 00:29:25.100
and how users will
contribute to those objects

00:29:25.100 --> 00:29:27.000
is really one of
the first things you should do

00:29:27.000 --> 00:29:29.801
when trying to sketch out
your particular gadg--

00:29:29.801 --> 00:29:31.033
the gadget you want to make.

00:29:31.033 --> 00:29:32.501
So did the user
just draw a picture?

00:29:32.501 --> 00:29:33.667
You know,
let 'em post it.

00:29:33.667 --> 00:29:36.267
Did the user just make
a donation to that site?

00:29:36.267 --> 00:29:38.367
Let them be featured
as the latest contributor.

00:29:38.367 --> 00:29:40.868
It's not always
just taking what they took

00:29:40.868 --> 00:29:42.300
and spitting it
right back at them.

00:29:42.300 --> 00:29:43.767
You can take what they took,

00:29:43.767 --> 00:29:45.334
mash it up
with other stuff,

00:29:45.334 --> 00:29:46.734
do some other things to it,

00:29:46.734 --> 00:29:48.634
and--or present it
back to them in a unique way

00:29:48.634 --> 00:29:50.334
that's different that the way
they contributed it.

00:29:50.334 --> 00:29:52.868
But, again,
thinking about

00:29:52.868 --> 00:29:54.868
just those pieces
of, you know--

00:29:54.868 --> 00:29:56.534
you get the--
kind of the nouns

00:29:56.534 --> 00:29:57.968
and then you start
to get the verb for

00:29:57.968 --> 00:29:59.434
"how did they give it to you,"

00:29:59.434 --> 00:30:00.734
and the verb for "how do you
give it back to them"

00:30:00.734 --> 00:30:02.968
by thinking about it
this way, I think.

00:30:02.968 --> 00:30:05.334
And I think also
when you think about,

00:30:05.334 --> 00:30:07.234
you know, kind of
each object or each action

00:30:07.234 --> 00:30:09.701
in this framework,
you start to think about

00:30:09.701 --> 00:30:11.334
each object or each action

00:30:11.334 --> 00:30:13.534
as a potentially
shareable moment.

00:30:13.534 --> 00:30:15.367
And I think, you know,
what this--

00:30:15.367 --> 00:30:17.000
this helps you not only
get a better idea

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:18.234
of what your gadget
should be about,

00:30:18.234 --> 00:30:20.167
but it helps just make
your gadget more social

00:30:20.167 --> 00:30:21.501
because of that.

00:30:21.501 --> 00:30:22.634
You're always thinking about,

00:30:22.634 --> 00:30:23.934
"Oh, what are users
creating in my gadget?"

00:30:23.934 --> 00:30:25.701
"Oh, what could users
potentially consume

00:30:25.701 --> 00:30:27.267
that other users
are creating?"

00:30:27.267 --> 00:30:29.434
And so you really start to,
I think--

00:30:29.434 --> 00:30:31.000
social features
start to pop out

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:32.567
kind of
of your gadget, you know?

00:30:32.567 --> 00:30:34.033
By thinking about
stuff in this way, I've--

00:30:34.033 --> 00:30:35.901
there's a few features
that I'm building

00:30:35.901 --> 00:30:37.501
