00:32:22.100 --> 00:32:24.601
the Google Friend Connect
APIs.

00:32:24.601 --> 00:32:27.400
And so there are
set networks here

00:32:27.400 --> 00:32:29.701
that are things like
traditional social networks

00:32:29.701 --> 00:32:31.667
that you go to
to interact with your friends.

00:32:31.667 --> 00:32:34.400
There are also sites here
such as LinkedIn

00:32:34.400 --> 00:32:36.767
which is more of a business
network that you go to

00:32:36.767 --> 00:32:38.634
to establish
business relationships.

00:32:38.634 --> 00:32:42.133
And not only are the--these
25+ networks around the world,

00:32:42.133 --> 00:32:44.734
but keep in mind
the 5 million web sites

00:32:44.734 --> 00:32:47.834
which are also
OpenSocial containers

00:32:47.834 --> 00:32:52.033
built on top
of Google Friend Connect.

00:32:52.033 --> 00:32:55.467
There are, however,
some technical differences

00:32:55.467 --> 00:32:58.434
between what you do
to build a gadget

00:32:58.434 --> 00:33:00.801
for a traditional
social network

00:33:00.801 --> 00:33:02.701
and what you would do
to build a gadget

00:33:02.701 --> 00:33:04.133
for Google Friend Connect.

00:33:04.133 --> 00:33:06.567
So I'm going to try to untangle
a little bit of that mess

00:33:06.567 --> 00:33:08.467
in the next couple
of slides here.

00:33:08.467 --> 00:33:11.234
Maybe it's not a mess,
but anyway,

00:33:11.234 --> 00:33:12.501
there's some differences.

00:33:12.501 --> 00:33:14.834
So first of all,

00:33:14.834 --> 00:33:16.467
the types of data--

00:33:16.467 --> 00:33:17.634
with Google Friend Connect,

00:33:17.634 --> 00:33:19.167
and with all
OpenSocial containers,

00:33:19.167 --> 00:33:20.834
you have some basic
types of data:

00:33:20.834 --> 00:33:22.634
profiles and friends,

00:33:22.634 --> 00:33:24.934
which have,
in Friend Connect, an I.D.,

00:33:24.934 --> 00:33:26.567
a name,
a thumbnail URL,

00:33:26.567 --> 00:33:29.868
activities and messages,
and application data

00:33:29.868 --> 00:33:32.400
that is specific
to your individual gadget

00:33:32.400 --> 00:33:34.000
or application.

00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:37.567
You can access all of this
using a couple different ways.

00:33:37.567 --> 00:33:41.033
You can access it
using client-side functionality,

00:33:41.033 --> 00:33:42.501
things like JavaScript,

00:33:42.501 --> 00:33:46.467
or in the new 0.9
implementation of OpenSocial--

00:33:46.467 --> 00:33:48.968
which Friend Connect,
as of today, supports.

00:33:48.968 --> 00:33:52.801
You can also access it
using OSML and Templates,

00:33:52.801 --> 00:33:54.534
which are
some different ways

00:33:54.534 --> 00:33:56.067
of developing applications.

00:33:56.067 --> 00:33:57.701
All three of these
allow you to do

00:33:57.701 --> 00:33:58.968
pretty much the same things,

00:33:58.968 --> 00:34:01.133
but the OSML and Templates

00:34:01.133 --> 00:34:03.634
allow you to do a little bit
easier development

00:34:03.634 --> 00:34:05.934
and make it a little bit
more performant.

00:34:05.934 --> 00:34:07.901
And then there's
the server-side access

00:34:07.901 --> 00:34:12.200
using REST
and RPC libraries.

00:34:12.200 --> 00:34:13.968
So who are the people

00:34:13.968 --> 00:34:16.601
that are involved
in your Friend Connect gadgets

00:34:16.601 --> 00:34:18.501
or in any OpenSocial gadget?

00:34:18.501 --> 00:34:24.033
Basically you have the viewer
and you have the owner.

00:34:24.033 --> 00:34:25.734
The viewer--

00:34:25.734 --> 00:34:27.601
in traditional
social networks,

00:34:27.601 --> 00:34:29.701
the viewer is
the authenticated user

00:34:29.701 --> 00:34:31.701
who is using your app.

00:34:31.701 --> 00:34:34.400
When--when
they're viewing it,

00:34:34.400 --> 00:34:36.367
it's the person
that's using it.

00:34:36.367 --> 00:34:37.701
In Google Friend Connect,

00:34:37.701 --> 00:34:39.367
the authen--
it's the same thing.

00:34:39.367 --> 00:34:40.601
It's the authenticated user

00:34:40.601 --> 00:34:42.300
who is viewing
your application.

00:34:42.300 --> 00:34:45.801
However, you need to really
remember the anonymous user.

00:34:45.801 --> 00:34:47.367
So on those, like,

00:34:47.367 --> 00:34:49.934
5 million Google Friend Connect
enabled sites,

00:34:49.934 --> 00:34:53.767
they each get, you know,
tons and tons of page views.

00:34:53.767 --> 00:34:55.701
And of those
tons and tons of page views,

00:34:55.701 --> 00:34:57.868
a lot of them
are actually going to be

00:34:57.868 --> 00:35:00.767
logged out users.

00:35:00.767 --> 00:35:03.234
You're hoping that--
and, you know,

00:35:03.234 --> 00:35:05.300
keeping in mind when
you're designing your gadgets

00:35:05.300 --> 00:35:08.367
that the logged in users
are the ones

00:35:08.367 --> 00:35:10.400
that are building the data

00:35:10.400 --> 00:35:11.901
for the logged out
users to view

00:35:11.901 --> 00:35:14.100
and making it interesting
even for the logged out users.

00:35:14.100 --> 00:35:16.968
So keep in mind
that the anonymous viewer

00:35:16.968 --> 00:35:18.467
is something special here

00:35:18.467 --> 00:35:19.701
with Google Friend
Connect gadgets.

00:35:19.701 --> 00:35:21.234
Usually
with traditional networks

00:35:21.234 --> 00:35:24.467
you don't have to worry
about that too much.

00:35:24.467 --> 00:35:27.200
So what information--when
you do have a logged in viewer,

00:35:27.200 --> 00:35:28.667
what information
do you have?

00:35:28.667 --> 00:35:32.000
You have the I.D.,
ABOUT_ME,

00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:34.033
PROFILE_URL,
and THUMBNAIL_URL.

00:35:34.033 --> 00:35:36.167
these are the core bits
of information

00:35:36.167 --> 00:35:39.934
that you need to use
to make a gadget more social.

00:35:39.934 --> 00:35:42.801
The I.D. is simply
a long string of numbers,

00:35:42.801 --> 00:35:47.501
the ABOUT_ME is a string
that the user defines

00:35:47.501 --> 00:35:49.267
to describe,
like, you know,

00:35:49.267 --> 00:35:52.167
in a Twitter sort of
140 characters or less usually

00:35:52.167 --> 00:35:54.667
string about
who the person is,

00:35:54.667 --> 00:35:56.701
a PROFILE_URL,

00:35:56.701 --> 00:35:58.868
which allows you
to link off to their profile,

00:35:58.868 --> 00:36:03.100
and a THUMBNAIL_URL,
which is their picture.

00:36:03.100 --> 00:36:05.200
In traditional
social networks,

00:36:05.200 --> 00:36:07.400
you have some additional
profile data.

00:36:07.400 --> 00:36:09.901
So you can see
some listed here.

00:36:09.901 --> 00:36:11.734
The darker ones are ones

00:36:11.734 --> 00:36:13.968
that aren't currently available
in Google Friend Connect

00:36:13.968 --> 00:36:17.501
but are available on some
traditional social networks.

00:36:17.501 --> 00:36:21.667
But things like, you know,
SMOKER or DRINKER--

00:36:21.667 --> 00:36:23.501
are those things
that you really care about

00:36:23.501 --> 00:36:24.767
when you're building
your gadgets?

00:36:24.767 --> 00:36:26.367
Probably not,

00:36:26.367 --> 00:36:30.133
unless you're trying
to advertise tobacco products

00:36:30.133 --> 00:36:32.801
or advertise alcohol.

00:36:32.801 --> 00:36:34.801
Those are things
that you just don't care about.

00:36:34.801 --> 00:36:37.234
So Friend Connect
does allow you access

00:36:37.234 --> 00:36:39.868
to the core bits of data,
which are available

00:36:39.868 --> 00:36:44.334
regardless of what site
the user is connected to

00:36:44.334 --> 00:36:47.000
for their profile
in Friend Connect.

00:36:47.000 --> 00:36:48.868
So in addition
to the viewer,

00:36:48.868 --> 00:36:50.234
you have the owner.

00:36:50.234 --> 00:36:51.834
In traditional networks,

00:36:51.834 --> 00:36:54.267
the owner is the user
who installed the app

00:36:54.267 --> 00:36:57.100
that is currently
being viewed.

00:36:57.100 --> 00:36:59.667
It's really the same thing
with Friend Connect

00:36:59.667 --> 00:37:01.300
but there's a little bit
of a difference here.

00:37:01.300 --> 00:37:04.868
The user that installed the app
is really the site.

00:37:04.868 --> 00:37:07.234
So in the example of,
you know,

00:37:07.234 --> 00:37:08.434
a traditional
social network,

00:37:08.434 --> 00:37:10.801
you don't have
an I.D. number

00:37:10.801 --> 00:37:12.033
that represents a web site.

00:37:12.033 --> 00:37:13.400
In Friend Connect, you do.

00:37:13.400 --> 00:37:15.334
So this long number here

00:37:15.334 --> 00:37:19.334
is the I.D. for
the chatbotc.com web site.

00:37:19.334 --> 00:37:22.467
That's a web site that
has a blog and all on it

00:37:22.467 --> 00:37:25.400
from one of our other
developer advocates.

00:37:25.400 --> 00:37:27.100
And in addition to that,

00:37:27.100 --> 00:37:29.534
you have a PROFILE_URL
for that site.

00:37:29.534 --> 00:37:31.934
So if you look
at that site's friends,

00:37:31.934 --> 00:37:34.734
it's actually
all the members of the site.

00:37:34.734 --> 00:37:36.667
And that's--so that's
some interesting information

00:37:36.667 --> 00:37:40.067
that you can get by looking
at the friends of a user,

00:37:40.067 --> 00:37:43.901
which in this case
is the web site.

00:37:43.901 --> 00:37:47.100
So I'm going to talk to you
about a couple different ways

00:37:47.100 --> 00:37:49.467
to use the page context

00:37:49.467 --> 00:37:51.834
to build better gadgets.

00:37:51.834 --> 00:37:54.267
Just as you wouldn't expect
to see a toilet

00:37:54.267 --> 00:37:55.801
sitting out
in the middle of the street,

00:37:55.801 --> 00:37:58.033
you also probably
wouldn't expect to see

00:37:58.033 --> 00:38:00.334
a Tetris game
on a stock blog

00:38:00.334 --> 00:38:01.901
or, you know,
something like that.

00:38:01.901 --> 00:38:03.767
So you need
to keep that in mind

00:38:03.767 --> 00:38:05.934
as you're building
your gadgets.

00:38:05.934 --> 00:38:07.267
You can keep in mind

00:38:07.267 --> 00:38:10.033
the content of the page
or the blog.

00:38:10.033 --> 00:38:11.567
In this case,
I'm going to show you

00:38:11.567 --> 00:38:14.434
some APIs
that exist in Blogger.

00:38:14.434 --> 00:38:17.067
So Blogger implements
Google Friend Connect

00:38:17.067 --> 00:38:19.868
for many, many blogs
and it's by--

00:38:19.868 --> 00:38:23.000
implemented by default
for new blogs.

00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:25.167
And Blogger
provides some APIs

00:38:25.167 --> 00:38:26.868
for Friend Connect gadgets

00:38:26.868 --> 00:38:28.767
which allow you
to get access

00:38:28.767 --> 00:38:31.167
to the content
of the posts in the blog

00:38:31.167 --> 00:38:33.634
and the content of
the comments in the blog.

00:38:33.634 --> 00:38:37.834
Why might you
want to use this?

00:38:37.834 --> 00:38:40.667
So imagine this--
you have a blog.

00:38:40.667 --> 00:38:43.434
You only have
a couple of followers

00:38:43.434 --> 00:38:44.901
and you have some friends

00:38:44.901 --> 00:38:48.300
that are also
following your blog.

00:38:48.300 --> 00:38:50.467
And your blog has
pictures of your puppy.

00:38:50.467 --> 00:38:52.501
Think about
this conversation here.

00:38:52.501 --> 00:38:56.334
You know, someone comments,
"Digit is so cute."

00:38:56.334 --> 00:38:58.234
If you haven't figured it out,
Digit's my dog.

00:38:58.234 --> 00:39:00.734
But some people were commenting,
"Digit is so cute."

00:39:00.734 --> 00:39:03.968
John says, "Too girly.
I want a real dog."

00:39:03.968 --> 00:39:06.868
And believe me,
people have told me this.

00:39:06.868 --> 00:39:08.901
And Jane says,
"Awww, John is nuts."

00:39:08.901 --> 00:39:11.267
And then there's a conversation
that goes back and forth

00:39:11.267 --> 00:39:12.601
in the blog on the comments.

00:39:12.601 --> 00:39:14.300
But what do you
really care about?

00:39:14.300 --> 00:39:17.734
In this case, you know,
I have a very popular blog

00:39:17.734 --> 00:39:20.234
with, I don't know,
420-some--

00:39:20.234 --> 00:39:24.501
420--4 mill--
thousand comments on it.

00:39:24.501 --> 00:39:27.033
You really care about
filtering that information

00:39:27.033 --> 00:39:29.901
down to what
is interesting to you,

00:39:29.901 --> 00:39:31.734
and oftentimes,
what is interesting to you

00:39:31.734 --> 00:39:34.400
is the comments that
were made by your friends.

00:39:34.400 --> 00:39:37.567
So I care that Jane said,
"Digit is so cute,"

00:39:37.567 --> 00:39:39.567
and I care that she said,
"John is nuts."

00:39:39.567 --> 00:39:42.367
But I really don't care
that John said

00:39:42.367 --> 00:39:45.133
Digit is "too girly"
and he wants "a real dog,"

00:39:45.133 --> 00:39:47.801
because I like my dog
perfectly fine.

00:39:47.801 --> 00:39:51.901
All right, so here's
